==Consequences== As consequence of the negative depiction of Colombia and the Colombian people, Colombians are often subject of prejudice and discrimination in several countries.<ref>*(Spanish) Narcotráfico: un pretexto para la discriminación de los migrantes colombianos y de otras nacionalidades Colombia, Documentos De La Red {{ISSN|1900-639X}}, 2007 vol:2 fasc: 1 págs: 74 - 92 Autores: WILLIAM MEJIA OCHOA,</ref> some examples include: * Colombians are among the main targets of [[xenophobia|xenophobes]] and [[neonazi]] attacks in [[Europe]], especially in [[Spain]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.estereofonica.com/xenofobia-contra-los-colombianos-en-espana-especial-de-septimo-dia-y-toda-la-programacion-del-canal-caracol/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-09-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090529074407/http://www.estereofonica.com/xenofobia-contra-los-colombianos-en-espana-especial-de-septimo-dia-y-toda-la-programacion-del-canal-caracol/ |archivedate=2009-05-29 |df= }}</ref> and [[France]].<ref name="elespectador.com">{{cite web|author=Ricardo Abdahllah |url=http://www.elespectador.com/impreso/internacional/articuloimpreso146569-dura-golpiza-colombiano-paris |title=Dura golpiza a colombiano en París |language=es |website=Elespectador.Com |date=2009-06-18 |accessdate=2017-05-18}}</ref> Spanish [[paramedics]] have reportedly refused to provide care to Colombian victims of such events.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lacomunidad.elpais.com/jose-penagos1/2007/11/7/otro-aberrante-caso-xenofobia-contra-colombiano |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-09-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090722070418/http://lacomunidad.elpais.com/jose-penagos1/2007/11/7/otro-aberrante-caso-xenofobia-contra-colombiano |archivedate=2009-07-22 |df= }}</ref> [[Police]] have been reported to refuse received complaints of the victims.<ref name="elespectador.com"/> * "We don't sell to Colombians" signs are common in [[Ecuador]]ian stores{{Citation needed|date=November 2010}}. [[Lynching]] and [[necklacing]] of Colombian people have been reported in [[Ecuador]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eltiempo.com/archivo/documento/CMS-3812514|title=Los brotes de xenofobia en Ecuador contra colombianos toman tintes preocupantes|first=Casa Editorial El|last=Tiempo|website=El Tiempo}}</ref> Police and media are accused of creating the image that every [[:wikt:delinquent|delinquent]] band has Colombian leaders. Police reportedly refuse to receive denounces of crimes against Colombians.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.adital.com.br/Site/noticia2.asp?lang=ES&cod=6986 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-09-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706151624/http://www.adital.com.br/Site/noticia2.asp?lang=ES&cod=6986 |archivedate=2011-07-06 |df= }}</ref> Colombian children are often rejected from schools, and "preventive" [[battery (crime)|battering]] of unrelated Colombians in the vicinity of a crime scene has been reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecuadorinmediato.com/Noticias/news_user_view/ecuadorinmediato_noticias--65354|title=HOY (Quito) Ecuador: xenofobia contra colombianos|website=Ecuadorinmediato.com}}</ref> * Colombian [[passport]] often makes the person suspicious to international custom authorities{{Citation needed|date=November 2010}}. Extensive [[cavity search]]es, dismantling of [[luggage]]s, [[clothing]] and personal items and Illegal retention in the airports without food or basic facilities have been reported<ref>{{Cite journal | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=xJnSlakRWe8C&lpg=PA100&dq=discriminacion%20colombianos%20aeropuertos&pg=PA88#v=onepage&q=&f=false | title = Informe Sos Racismo 2006 | isbn = 9788474266382 | date = 2003-04-25| author1 = Racismo | first1 = S.O.S. }}</ref>
