A 2011 poll shows that 66% of Finnish respondents considered [[Finland]] to be a [[racist]] country but only 14% admitted to being racists themselves.<ref name="HS">{{Cite web | url=http://www.hs.fi/english/article/Poll+Majority+of+Finns+see+Finland+as+racist+country/1135269860316 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130211025059/http://www.hs.fi/english/article/Poll+Majority+of+Finns+see+Finland+as+racist+country/1135269860316 | archivedate=11 February 2013 | title=Poll: Majority of Finns see Finland as racist country | work=[[Helsingin Sanomat]]}}</ref> Minority groups getting the most negative attitudes were [[Finnish Kale]], Somalis and ethnic groups mostly consisting of Muslims.<ref name="HS"/>

In December 2012 the Finnish Police reported an increase in cases of racism and related physical abuse.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://yle.fi/uutiset/police_report_increase_in_racism_and_abuse/6422538|title=Police report: Increase in racism and abuse|work=Yle Uutiset|accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref> In February 2013 researchers of racism and multiculturalism reported an increase in the number of threats and abuse.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://yle.fi/uutiset/racism_researchers_at_university_of_eastern_finland_are_subjected_to_abuse/6493243|title=Unions concerned over abuse of racism researchers|work=Yle Uutiset|accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref> In January 2013 [[Save the Children]] reported that immigrant children are facing an increasing amount of racist abuse.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://yle.fi/uutiset/immigrant_children_face_racism/6445482|title=Immigrant children face racism|work=Yle Uutiset|accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref> In June 2011 a researcher reported an increase in the amount of racist violence targeting children and teenagers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://yle.fi/uutiset/racism_increasingly_aimed_at_children_and_teens/5387317|title=Racism increasingly aimed at children and teens|work=Yle Uutiset|accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref>

According to [[European Commission against Racism and Intolerance]] (ECRI) of the [[Council of Europe]], neither the [[Ombudsman for Minorities]] nor [[Advisory Board for Ethnic Relations]] have the financial and human resources to effectively perform according to their mandate. There is a [[National Non-Discrimination and Equality Tribunal]], but it cannot order compensation to victims of racial discrimination.{{sfn|Council of Europe|2013|p=7}} The legal provisions of the [[Aliens' Act]] are discriminatory and subject ethnic minorities to [[racial profiling]] by the [[Police of Finland|police]].{{sfn|Council of Europe|2013|p=8}}

The majority of people in Finland are ignorant about issues concerning the [[Sami people|Sami]] minority. Sami issues are not taught at school to a satisfactory level, according to ECRI.{{sfn|Council of Europe|2013|p=8}} ECRI has criticized Finland for not having ratified the [[Indigenous and Tribal Peoples Convention, 1989|ILO-convention 169 on Indigenous and Tribal Peoples]].{{sfn|Council of Europe|2013|p=7}}

The [[Somali community in Finland]] as well as the [[Finnish Kale|Finnish Roma]] face discrimination and racism. [[Russians in Finland]] are discriminated against in employment.{{sfn|Council of Europe|2013|p=8}}

